<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A graphics standard for <a title="IBM-Compatible Computer" href="IBM-Compatible_Computer">IBM-compatible computer</a>s that provided 1024 x 768-<a title="Pixel" href="Pixel">pixel</a> resolution and a display of 256 colors for color monitors. XGA superseded <a title="VGA" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/VGA">VGA</a> and the earlier <a title="EGA" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/EGA">EGA</a> and <a title="CGA" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/CGA">CGA</a>. 
</p>
